# Automate Blog Post Registration

To respond to the user's request for automation, we will create a script that scans the directory for blog posts and rebuilds the index file ([blog-posts.js](file:///C:/Users/maiku/.gemini/antigravity/blog-posts.js)). This allows "posting" (registering) entries simply by creating the HTML file and running this update script.

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] [update-blog-index.ps1](file:///C:/Users/maiku/.gemini/antigravity/update-blog-index.ps1)
- Scans for `post*.html`.
- Extracts the title from the `<title>` tag.
- Preserves existing dates from [blog-posts.js](file:///C:/Users/maiku/.gemini/antigravity/blog-posts.js) if available to prevent existing posts from having their dates reset.
- Uses file creation time for new posts (like [post6.html](file:///C:/Users/maiku/.gemini/antigravity/post6.html) if not yet indexed).
- Generates a fresh [blog-posts.js](file:///C:/Users/maiku/.gemini/antigravity/blog-posts.js) sorted by post number (descending).

